HSBC Division Agrees to Manage Allianz’s Pension Fund in Turkey

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-06-30T14:11:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/hsbc-division-agrees-to-manage-allianz-s-pension-fund-in-turkey.html
HSBC Holding Plc’s Turkish asset
manager said it agreed to manage  Allianz SE (ALV) ’s Istanbul-based
pension fund.  HSBC Portfoy Yonetimi AS will be managing 3 billion liras
($1.85 billion) of assets including 500 million liras from the
premiums collected by Allianz’s life insurer in  Turkey , HSBC
Portfoy Chief Executive Officer Namik Aksel said in a telephone
interview today.  Turkey’s private pension system is expected to have 300,000
participants this year with the number of policy holders at 2.6
million and a total fund size of 15 billion liras, Solmaz Altin,
chief financial officer of Allianz’s Turkish operation, said in
an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 